President Joseph R. Biden, Jr. of the United States joined the European Council to discuss the coordinated response to Russia's military aggression in Ukraine. They reviewed efforts to impose economic costs on Russia and Belarus and discussed the possibility of additional measures. Humanitarian assistance and access to those affected by the violence were also emphasized. International investigations into the atrocities were welcomed, along with efforts to reduce dependence on Russian fossil fuels and accelerate the transition to clean energy. Strengthening democratic resilience in Ukraine, Moldova, and the wider Eastern partnership region was highlighted, as well as the importance of transatlantic security and defense through NATO-EU cooperation.